{
  "texts": [
    "From Fig. 13, the Naïve Bayes model had performed the poorest among the models in accurately classifying the CP (Children Playing) class and has achieved poor results in comparison to other classifier models.",
    "This can be due to noise present in the audio samples and the internal processing of the Naïve Bayes model for determining the class to which the audio sample should belong.",
    "However, this does not imply that Naïve Bayes is a not-so-good approach for classification.",
    "Some studies show that Naïve Bayes performs very well in other fields [52,53].",
    "Similarly, in Fig. 14, FA (Falling) class has been poorly classified by Naïve Bayes and KNN model."
  ]
}